Sam Houston remains undefeated with win over Highlands 1 / 1 Back to Gallery Thanks to a relentless defense and a well-timed play on special teams, Sam Houston moved into sole possession of first place in District 28-5A with a 34-6 victory over Highlands on Thursday at Alamo Stadium.
The Hurricanes, the areaâ€™s No. 3 sub-6A team, yielded 205 total yards, forced three turnovers and scored on a deflected punt to improve to 7-0 overall and 4-0 in district.
